The paper presents a novel approach to incremental learning and problem-solving, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of search algorithms, which could place it in the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) or programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper involves experiments with Towers of Hanoi, which is a classic problem in computer science and algorithms, suggesting a possible fit with the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
